,Not Recommended,253250,34694325,Posted: 2 September,all,Adam,"As you can see I've put a decent number of hours into the game (58 at the time of review).  I will likely continue playing it however I can't recommend it at this time.  I realize that it's an early access game and I expect bugs to happen.  The one glaring issue that prevents me from recommending this game is the how laggy it gets above 20 hearthlings.  I don't know if it's the number of hearthlings or if this is simply a correlation to the amount of development you're able to achieve around the same time you get to 20 hearthlings.  About that time the game goes from moving along smoothly to a stuttering mess.  I have a decent PC and I've watched a resource monitor on my other screen.  The game taps about 4-8gb of RAM and takes up approximately 30% of my CPU.  I've hunted around on forums and there doesn't seem to be a consensus on what's causing the slowdown.  Most of what I found attributed it to walling in your town and somehow that creates pathing issues, others have said it's simply the amount of time the game has been running and a restart will clear it up.  Either way, I would like to continue to grow a town and summon some Orcs to challenge but it's just not fun when the game looks like stop motion photography instead of running smoothly.Developers:  If you're reading this I would like for you to know that I will happily change this review to a Yes when the mid-late game lag issues are resolved."
