,Recommended,253250,27796925,"Posted: 27 November, 2016",all,Cytokinin,"So... Stonehearth.It's Early Access, and noticably so. Bugs, the fps drops lower the further you progress, your Hearthlings don't respond to commands, yada yada. Still, these bugs don't ruin the experience. Lower your expectations, it's not a fully completed game.The -in my opinion- biggest problem with this game, is the lack of difficulty scaling. Normal mode starts slightly difficult, but it gets too easy very quickly. There is a hard mode, but it suffers the same fate, except that it starts out very difficult.Once you've set up your farms and hunting grounds, your walls, your houses, there's not much that can hurt you anymore.Monsters don't destroy structures, which is both good and bad.Good, because given how clunky and weird the building system is, having walls get holes in them would be annoying to repair, unless hearthlings do it automatically, and then it becomes pointless.Bad, because they don't destroy anything. Put up some picket fences around a goblin camp without them attacking? Good job, they can't do anything to you now.With having said all this, the blue thumbs up might look strange, since all I've said are the negatives.But now that they're out of the way, I've got to say, this game is fantastic.The things that work, work really well.Having multiple combat squads, for example. Easy to assign, easy to control, incredibly satisfying to attack monsters from multiple angles, with seperate squads. Mining is easy, and the slice system is a godsend (and a necessity) for making multi-layer mines. The x-ray mode (it's not for finding ores easily, don't worry) is also fantastic. Being able to see your structures without all the other stuff in the way, it's great.And there is so much more good to be said about this game.Hearthling (they're the settlers, for clarification) professions are nice, and really allows for a personal story. Have a Trapper who has been there, doing the same work, for al the days he's been in the village? Let him retire, by making him a Shepherd (not saying all shepherds have easy lives, just that the hearthling ones seem to be in no rush, as they slowly walk through your village)!Maybe your farmer has farmed for so long that they've inevitably gotten exquisite knowledge about what they're doing?Promote them to a cook, and let them fill the metaphorical stomachs of your hearthlings!So, do I recommend this game?Obviously. But I also recommend patience when playing it. Everything won't go 100% perfectly, but if you work past the bugs, you'll have a fantastic time."
,Recommended,253250,29154147,Posted: 9 January,all,jrizzle8769,"I want to love this game sooo much. It has so much going for it. There are just a few flaws in logistics that are keeping it from being perfect.The AI is terrible - My workers are currently all standing around ""idle"" while I have crap everywhere that needs to be collected (ores, wood, wool, farm goods). There is no way to direct them to do what they are supposed to be doing.  I end up having to use the cancel option to permanently delete the items even though some are super rare. Amazing when i tell the workers to delete the item they are all over it....There is no way to edit the land once you have mined it. If you make a mistake...oh well...i hope you are not OCD like me. I currently have the grass layer near my village floating in the sky because either i made a mistake or my workers did not do as they were told.Finally, once food starts going bad in your storage it is a nightmare. Your workers do not remove this rotten food on their own accord. You must manually delete each basket of rotten food. Im at the point now where I literally spend a quarter of my day scoping out the food storage to remove these rotten baskets.This game is definitley on the right track but I would still wait until release to see if these kinks will be worked out. If they are this would likely become one of my favorite games in this genre on steam.TL:DR- AI needs work- Need an option to turn off rotting food or make workers remove it on their own- Need a few more land editing options in case you make a mistake (or your workers)This is a great title and I hope they continue to improve these imperfections. Giving it a thumbs up for encouragement to the Devs!"
