,Recommended,253250,29107081,Posted: 7 January,all,"New Player, Be Nice","TLDR:Game I thought I wouldn't like because I've never played Minecraft, but ended up falling in love with it. This game is really amazing and it's still in alpha/early access. 8/10 and worth the price even in Early Access.My Impression:My first impression of Stonehearth after watching their presentation video was that I didn't think I would enjoy playing it. Although I have never played Minecraft, the graphics reminded me of it. I never really got into Minecraft because I prefer single-player games and because of the graphics. I paid $19.99 for the game during the Steam Winter Sale, and I thought I was probably going to refund it due to the game not being worth the price. I decided I would buy it during the sale and if I didn't like it I would refund it. I was wrong, I love the game. DansGaming also had the same feeling as me. He thought it was going to be a mediocre game and was only going to stream it for a bit. He ended up falling in love with it as well.Positive:+ City builder but with a mix of RPG elements and character classes+ Unique party system to manage your civilians easiers+ Multiple races and scenarios to play with+ Crafting and building system are near perfection, well done+ Fun quests and random encounters+ Different modes if you want to just build or battle enemies while you build+ Relaxing gameplay+ Great soundtrack+ UI is aesthetically pleasing+ Overall extremely well polished for an Early Access titleNegatives:- Optimization could be a bit better, depending on how high your citizen setting is at (I found my sweet spot at 22 citizens), performance can be slowed down. Fire effects also slow the game down.- Using the house builder at the moment is very unintuitive and not easily done- Could use more built in premade buildings- Bugs, things you would expect in an early access title- No steam workshop for building blueprints- No cloud saves- Added some suggestions to the developers at (https://discourse.stonehearth.net/t/suggestions-after-playing-about-15-hours/27403)Very Good Game:8/10I have refunded many games on Steam before. I am often very skeptical of the prices developers list their games at, but I can say that this game is worth it's price even in Early Access."
