76561197997861646,Not Recommended,253250,33282364,Posted: 5 July,all,mallenlane,"This tech demo is a messThe primary feature is the freeform building; otherwise it's dwarf fortress. You design voxel blueprints, hearthlings build. Construction happens with such fine granularity that pathing and incompletion errors are common. Buildings don't get finished; hearthlings get stuck in places. Problems the developer has spent much of the past 4 years trying to fix- without success.Did they ask themselves if every individual voxel really needs to get placed by a hearthling? Simplify so a similar appearance of building happens, yet is more successful in completing? Maybe cheat a little, and teleport stuck Hearthlings after several minutes prevented from doing a task? Any design concessions that a sane developer would make to ensure that both they and the players can continue to progress? Nope.Obsessed with perfecting one concept of how things get done, with no room for compromise, they hammer away at the same few problems and features, with no end in sight. Honestly, the developer needs to be reorganized, or it will never get anywhere."
