e lack of variety in general but like I said earlier they don't make this game unplayable. But I also have very positive thoughts on this game. I love what they recently added in Alpha 21 with the traits that your hearthlings have and earlier (I think Alpha 20) where you can personlize their looks rather than just randomizing and hoping they don't look too out of whack.Even though it is voxel the shading and how clear the graphics are really impress me. I think especially for a voxel that the game looks good as well (better graphics option in settings). The music also is very soothing and I feel enhances the mood rather than the audio previously set to damage you ears.I would reccomend this game to anyone to love city builders, farming simualtors, or even history since the game is based upon a group of seven Hearthlings that come to settle and make discoveries.This game is only in Alpha 21 so there is always going to be more until the final verison will be published. I really hope that if anyone happens to read this at all that you find my suggestions helpful to you and that I had a positive impact on your thoughts to Stonehearth. I have found Stonehearth to be a game where the devolopers are constantly prorgressing and able to give us something new each time. Thanks for reading to the very end of my long review. :)"
