,Recommended,253250,17273247,"Posted: 28 July, 2015",all,The Mouse,"This game is incredibly adorable, but in its current state it drops you into an amazing little world with only tooltips to guide you. It's very fun for those who like a splash of adventure, exploration, town defending and building your own unique world from the square foundation. However, be sure to check out the community StoneHearth website for Getting Started info and keep these few things in mind when you get started!1.) Hearthlings are all unique little characters with their own stats. Before you assign Professions always check their stats to see if they'll be a good match for what you want them to do. Footsoldiers need a good Body stat and higher Courage or else they'll not defend much of anything!2.) Don't forget to have at least one Carpenter, one Trapper/Farmer, and one Fighter at the beginning of the game. Keep at least 3 to 4 Workers in order to keep general building/clearing tasks moving!3.) It's in alpha. You're going to crash. So much. Don't play this unless you've got a lot of patience to experiment and hate to risk losing your progress and remember to save often. If you find a bug, report it so the Devs know what's going on!"
