76561197970960417,Not Recommended,253250,21375250,"Posted: 21 February, 2016",all,Qing,"Meh.  It's cute; like you might think you are going to get something like minecraft but it's really not.  You can dig blocks out of the dirt but that's just to harvest randomly placed ores.  And, you have to be really attentive to how you give your dig instructions or they will dig a hole they can't get out of... and starve without warning.  Beyond that it's kind of like any other crafting game; you have to have your tradespeople level up before they can build certain things, or unlock more types of trades/specialties. What you cannot do is control any of the villagers.  The only controls you have are your build queue, you can designate areas for mining, loot collection, you can set up zones for farming plants, animals, trapping, (much like Sim City)  and you can order an 'alert' where all the villagers run to your designated safe-zone, marked by a flag.  You can relocate the flag as your village changes.  The only villagers you can slightly control are the footmen, which have 3 or 4 basic instructions that really all amount to the same thing... ""move here and fight any threats"".  The threats are nothing too severe... the occasional zombie, golem etc that wants to steal your stuff or kill your villagers.  Oh, and don't forget to cancel your footmen's orders when the fighting is done or they will stick to their new post, and starve without comment.The pace is ponderous... it has 2 speeds, neither of which is fast enough to make the time go by, but the accelerated speed is too fast to be able to react well to some of the hostiles that show up.  It'd be nice if it had instad of 1x/2x, it had 5x/10x and option to drop to normal speed when a zombie alert shows up.So... it looks like a good game for younger kids but I think the crafting system and build-requirements are just a touch too complex for them.  Anyone else may enjoy it until they come to the realization... this is really all there is."
