76561198038622566,Recommended,253250,23702542,"Posted: 22 June, 2016",all,imajor,"TL;DR Lovely game with problems, but highly recommended.This game is similar to Gnomoria, there are some important differences:- graphic is much better (I like retro graphic, but Gnomoria was too much for me)- game mechanics are simpler, or at least it is much easier to understand- buildings!!!I don't deeply know Gnomoria, so excuse me if this is not a correct list. In my opinion these were the three most annoying things in Gnomoria, so I was really happy when I found StoneHearth.Pros:- lovely graphic and atmosphere- the settlement looks pretty cool with all the interesting buildings- classes and abilities are interestingCons:- still alpha, so lots of features are not finished (I hope underworld will be improved, ores will not be just a random drop), there are bugs, balancing issues. But development is active, there are releases every week, so I don't worry much about these.- biggest issue for me are the buildings (this is in the same time the best feature of the game). So you first have to design the house (or use a template), and then your hearthlings will build it. First problem is that quite often they cannot build the house (this unfortunately happens with the templates as well). Second problem is that the game won't give you any warning or error message, the only thing you see is that the building is just paused. There are scaffoldings around the house, some walls are missing, but no one is doing nothing. I couldn't figure out what is wrong. The best thing I could do is that I built a few ladders here and there, maybe they were not able to reach some parts, but that didn't help. But the worst thing is that there is nothing you can do, you will have a half ready house with scaffoldings in the middle of your nice village. If you don't like that (I didn't) then the only option is to reload an old save where the building wasn't at all designed. That wasn't really a viable solution for me. There is a console command which erases a building, but it won't clean up the scaffolding, and also the base of the building will still be there (the hole in the ground). My feeling is that the devs were too optimistic about this type of building, I guess they think that there are problems, they can solve it easily for the next version, no need for error message or any tool which would help players work around a failed building. And then the next release comes, and there are still lots of buildings not correctly building. I think this is not a new issue, many recent releases had this. But I thrust them, I hope sooner or later they will be able to solve this, and players will be able to build a very nice village."
