76561197984842577,Recommended,253250,25139492,"Posted: 25 August, 2016",all,Hulk Hodn,"Through there are a few bugs here and there, it seems that the Dev Team is working on it all the time. Major releases with excellent content every month or so and a roadmap with great features to come! Best Building/Mining/Survival Voxel-Game since Minecraft."
,Recommended,253250,25138475,"Posted: 25 August, 2016",all,achedb0b,"pretty awesome game where you take control of a town of blocky individuals, who can take on quite a few different roles depending on their stats. They build buildings, mine, and craft items. If you want a game that is cute and you can design your own buildings and control a little town then this is the game.That said, there are some glaring issues I see with it. The whole way you design a new building is in my opinion quite badly done, you can't choose how high you want the walls and they are all encompassing, so you can't really have a 3 walled kind of thing. The main issue with it though is once you've designed a bulding, and then set it to be built you cannot edit it or demolish it. You'll need to use a console command just to do so, which is far from ideal.So the building system is:-Kind of basic, it really could be a lot more in depth, maybe being completely single block placement designing instead of the parts and pieces you can choose from.-Dodgy. I didn't like that I could only ""undo"" something, instead of having a proper deletion tool, the erase tool only seems to work on slabs and furniture. This can be frustrating at times. What's even more frustrating is slabs can actually clip through items and it does look quite terrible, but you don't notice it 'til the building is fully built, thus having to either deal with it's glitchy look, or demolish the entire building using cheats.The building system isn't the only thing that is annoying about the game, the mining can be just as annoying sometimes. Say you wanted to have a mined out grand hall in a mountain. Now though it may be difficult to see the ceiling in this game due to the camera being physically incapable, you do notice that the ceiling of a mined out area is quite low. If you want to have a higher ceiling it's near impossible to accomplish. Because of the fact you can't look up at the ceiling you can't select it to be mined, and even if you can the hearthlings have a great deal of trouble doing so. I planned on making a tunnel just over the room I wanted to heighten the ceiling of and one of them got stuck on a single block.So either players will need to have foresight or ingenuity to raise the roof or the devs should add a horizontal slice mode perhaps, which really would make my dwarfy self and brethren happy.Combat is quite great and the hearthlings themselves are pretty good at most activities. Though whenever they run away from battle it's only for 1 second, at which point they forget their♥♥♥♥♥kicking and return to fight the giant ogre they have no chance at beating.I'd suggest having proper retreats, perhaps to safety zones if the hearthling needs to run from battles, it would make micro managing them a bit easier.SPEAKING of micromanaging and combat. It at least for me is kind of unintuitive. Having groups is fine and all but then I have to select the combat tab, select the group, select what I want them to do and then send them off to do it, which is quite tedious. It's such a simple game yet so mindboggilingy hard to control at times.it really is a good game apart from these few things which make me almost pull my hair out sometimes, but that's probably just me. And it is in early access, hopefully they iron out all the bugs and the terrible building system in future. Otherwise there's alot to love about the game, and I think I'd recommend it at this time due to the devs updates, hopefully they continue to or I'll be changing my mind."
