,Recommended,253250,30863478,Posted: 31 March,all,Whooda,"It's a cute, animated, cube based Dwarf Fortress-lite city building/management sandbox game.Take the negative reviews with a grain of salt, most of these are people who either don't understand what ""alpha"" means, or think a small indie team can reasonably pump out a game in less then a few years AND make it bug free, optimized, and still fun.As I said it's in Alpha still, and has been for 2-3 years. If you're not patient and don't want to take part in the development of the game then don't get the game. If you can't handle the occasional UI crash or losing entire towns/saves don't get the game.However if you want to have some fun building a town up cube-by-cube with a consistently evolving building and crafting system, using ""Hearthlings"" who are as of this review beginning to gain unique personalities and needs, you should get this game. All while fighting off the occasional hordes of wolves, zombies, goblins, and cultists. Or you can opt for the creative mode and do whatever people do with no threat of losing. And you're contributing to the development with an active dev team who are (despite what seems to be some peoples opinion) working diligently on making this game as fun and bug free as possible before release. Watch in amazement as you post a bug to their forums and someone not only responds, but they fix it in the next release!TL;DR: It's a fun game in active alpha development which I would certainly recommend to friends if I had any."
