,Recommended,253250,30365355,Posted: 6 March,all,Kizu_Okami,"An interesting game to play. It has base building and the system it uses to determine if you can receive a new hearthling ensures you have an ideal amount of supplies to support your community. The pace of the mob spawns, strength, and attacks are balanced enough to provide a challenge but not to outright destroy everything you built within day 1. Another plus is how it has a somewhat story driven system that gives you main goals aside from any personal goals you may have for your communityThe base building is unique that it seperates everything into the basic details you may need to build a 2-story home, and if you choose, you can custom build a home brick by brick by using the slabs selection on the build menu.The game does have it's bugs though, looting can sometimes fail to work and would require a few different workarounds or console commands in order to allow an item to be looted. Sometimes while buiding structures your hearthlings may put an item on top of the building, and when they finish it, it will be stuck there unless you use console commands to move it.Another small downside is once a building is made it can no longer be edited. Things like wall decorations or furniture and workshops can not be placed on these areas once built but I am sure this can be fixed with console commands also.Overall it is a great game and after just buying it about 5 days ago, already have 11 hours logged into the game. Highly addictive, interesting, and fun."
