,Recommended,253250,25049041,"Posted: 21 August, 2016",all,geethereaper,"A very promising city-builder game. As of this review, it's still on its alpha version, so expect bugs. I get my hearthlings stuck here and there when mining and I've always got to put a ladder to ""rescue"" them. It's annoying. I hope they fix that. Here's what you get:Hearthlings - a collective name for your citizens. In order to gain more citizens, you've got to make improvements to your town to reach daily goals. Hearthlings have stats, and depending on those skill points, they could be suited to a particular job/task. It's still up to the player to assign what kind of work a hearthling would be doing, though.Enemies - you can get attacked or stolen by enemies. It's funny to think that these enemies could have their own camps/towns, too. I haven't played enough to the point of seeing a very good ""monster town"". But defeating them, you can pretty much loot their things.Resources - it's either you buy your things or you craft them from your own hard-earned materials. To get your raw materials and craft them into something else, you've got to rely on your hearthlings.Build Mode - there are a few building blueprints you can choose from and these pre-existing blueprints depend on your hearthlings' ancestry. Heck, if you don't like them, you could always customize your own! As your crafters become more experienced, you'd get to see new items you can use for building your buildings. So, it's not all laid down for you. I find that neat. We'd probably see more items for buildings as the game grows. It's unfortunate that once you finished constructing a building, you can no longer edit it. :(Quests - just a few, really.Opportunities for Trade - these pop out randomly as messages? You could always refuse if you don't like the deal. I wonder if we could have other towns to trade resources with? Even enemy towns? Haha. That'd be neat.Hmmm... I don't know if I've got everything down but those are the features I remember as of now. Anyway, you should check this out!"
