,Recommended,253250,25697538,"Posted: 25 September, 2016",all,Homiccus,"Berry nice game, I must admit. Tickles my fancy in more than one way.You will like it if you've ever played and liked:- Minecraft- Settlers- Banished- Dwarf Fortress (albeit you might find it a tad less complicated)It is a mixture of town building, resource management and roleplaying. The player is tasked with founding a new settlement with only seven settlers and limited equipment. One will have to provide means of getting resources and food and train your specialists to improve the quality of your settlers' lives and to keep your town safe from baddies that share the ground with the Hearthlings (albeit this could be turned off). If the town is doing well, it will attract new immigrants, which can be pressed into new roles. There is also an rpg-esque quest line (I believe one or two so far - more is promised), for which you will need to train and outfit a team ofadventurersmilitia.I particularly like the building system:- building templates for quick placement. Your workers will queue required components automatically;- every building can be customized to your liking and built to exact specs (ie. 'carpenter's house' template can be easily re-purposed for stonemason's workshop);- each construction is built brick-by-brick, complete with wooden scaffoldings, which are de-constructed after the job's finished;- multi-storey buildings are a thing.Clichés and subtle jokes run throughout the gameplay. Couple it with cute 3D pixel art and the result is rather refreshing.Yup,it is still in EA, it is still buggy, it is still incomplete. But nevertheless, so far, it is a lot of fun!Just don't take it too seriously."
