,Recommended,253250,16434209,"Posted: 15 June, 2015",all,jiffyracer,"Jiffyracer has come to town to Review!Overview:It is your job to create a bustling little town/village/city. You must make sure your folks have food, access to shelter, a bed, the necessities. You can create-your-own templates and build banks, supermarkets, castles, whatever your fancy. While the game is short on features at the moment, once you crack into this little gem, you'll find some fun customization.Experience:Rock meet face. Face meet middle of your sprite-body.I gaze at my fantastical creations as they're being created one block at a time. I'm impressed and amazed at how my little guys and gals go to work. I would be lying if I said I've not had my fair share of freezes, shut downs, and bugs. However, and this is a big damn however, I really actually enjoy this game. You can promote villagers to different jobs, or keep them as regular laborers. These different ""classes"" allow the player to generate new and exciting items for use within your village. Carpenters, masons, trappers, farmers, etc.; these are just a few of the jobs available to your villagers. Not every job is absolutely crucial, but it should be noted that if you want to have nice things, you should probably just give them a yob. Yes, I said yob. Because, farming. Take a minute and come back to it. Moving on, The lighting seems fairly well done as I enjoy seeing clouds and shadows dance across my creations. The sound is standard for this type of game, nothing immaculate, but neither mind-numbing either. Controls work as well as an early access city builder should, there are some chinks in the armor, but all-in-all it's acceptable as long as it's fixed in the long run.Review:As it currently stands, the gameplay is straightforward and sandbox. I enjoy this approach, but some may not. As I mentioned, the sound is basic, but not too busy. The controls are okay. I hate bugs. This is early access, I understand this is early access, hence why I'm giving the game-ending bugs a big nod. I will say that even though the bugs detract from the overall enjoyability of the title, seeing as this is early access, I am excited to see what is to come. As of the latest patch, I have been able to extend my playtime w/ this title w/out having as many faults or bugs crop up. I would give this game, in it's current state, a 7/10. I would recommend this title to friends who have patience, not controller-throwers. This is an interesting concept and I am happy to have supported Stonehearth. If you have any questions, feel free to respond.Thanks for taking the time to read my damned novella.Yobs."
