76561197970901534,Recommended,253250,27916269,"Posted: 27 November, 2016",all,Kaezin,"I'm the type of player that enjoys challenges, so my opinions are based off of treating Stonehearth as a survival game rather than a creative town-builder.If you enjoyed or were interested in games like Banished, Gnomoria, or Dwarf Fortress, then I highly suggest giving this game a shot.  It feels very similar to those games, but it has a much cleaner UI without sacrificing too much in terms of depth.  While the game isn't nearly as complicated as Dwarf Fortress (or even banished), there's still enough going on to keep you interested.Pros:Every decision you make has a consequence.For example, you have a limited number of workers available (at the beginning, at least), and you need to use them wisely.  At first I prioritized getting my economy up and going over having defenses (since I would convert the crafters into fighters whenever there was a threat), but that meant my fighters didn't gain levels very quickly.  As a result I couldn't use that sweet bronze platemail I made because no one was high enough level to use it.Another example: I decided to settle in a sweet defensive position, but I neglected to look for flax plants.  As a result I couldn't make any beginner armor for anyone and the rest of my economy started stalling.Free-form building crafting is fun and functional.  One of the stats used to determine whether or not you get a new villager is your village's value.  Placing things like windows, chairs, tables, etc. will increase the value of your village in addition to actually looking like a real village.  You can sculpt whatever you want without having to worry about whether you're doing things optimally.  Even things like nicer/expensive beds will improve the morale of your people, so it's in your best interest to do it.The UI is extremely clean compared to most base-building games that I've played.  There's no tutorial, either -- there's in-game help that detects if you're playing your first game, and that will guide you through the various aspects of the game.The soundtrack is very well done.Cons:I'd like to see more content added, but that's to be expected of an alpha.  I'd love to see more classes added.There's some bugs.  Nothing that has been game-breaking for me (although not being able to finish one of my buildings was frustrating).  Again, I'd expect that from an alpha.Other:* Art style.  I personally like the art style; it's cartoony enough to give the characters a unique style without going overboard on silly graphics.  I could see someone not liking the style, but whether or not you like the style should be easy to decide by looking at the demo screenshots."
76561198053027953,Recommended,253250,23467815,"Posted: 9 June, 2016",all,Scanmo,"great game cant wait for multiplayer, so much you can do,"
