,Recommended,253250,17309261,"Posted: 30 July, 2015",all,Eisler485,"*Art Style* 9/10I love how they make the Low Poly look beautiful.  There are a few minor issues causing the graphics to bug out but I believe that is an issue with the Settings.  It isnt anything to snuff at though.  I dont think this game would work with any other Graphic Style.*Gameplay*  10/10You have 3 difficulties Peaceful, Normal, and Hard.  Depending on how you want to play it is your choice.  I personaly like bonding with my Village and facing hardships at the same time so I go with Normal.  But if I want to just unwind I'll choose the Peaceful Gamemode.  Hard was made to test your moxy and test your limits by hitting you hard.*Depth*  10/10Again depends on how you play.  The more of a personality you give your characters/villagers the more involved and emotionally attached you get to them.  It makes you feel like your part of the village if you get involved.  Each character has unique Characteristics and looks (unless you change their looks).  Everything in this game is customizable.*Mechanics*  7.5/10The controls work alomst perfectly, expect the camera controls which is pretty much the entire game.  Scrolling and moving the camera around the X and Z axis is difficult to get used to.  The rotation of the camera is really hard to get used to as well and I've been playing for X amount of hours now.   There is no way to adjust the Y axis of the camera you can only move it around a pinpoint on the X/Z axis of the game.  (I have an Post Note down below as well)*Re-playability*  9/10As I stated earlier there are three gamemodes and everything is costomizable.  Once you get used to one difficulty you can move to the next.  Every world is random, every Character is random, no two times when you play are every alike.The rest is up to you I highly recommend buying this game!-Game Feature Ideas-~A Option to adjust the priority you're hearths complete Jobs.  Example, Hearths think Building is more important than Mining so they would Build instead of Mine."
