,Recommended,253250,16652759,"Posted: 23 June, 2015",all,Diz,"TLDR: This game is a joy to play and the review section is full of inpatient children that want their new shiny toy now and don't feel like waiting.This game is so much fun, I love gettin on now and again just to make a new small town and try new ideas I've had that day. I wanted to write this review because I've seen so many people write things such as ""this game has been in early access for 2 years..... It will never be finished, thumbs down"" and also ""as a backer for this game I feel let down..... its still not done"". I am not here to insult the community, but rather just say a few things that I feel you should know. Games take a long time to make. It could be a year or less. Or it could be 5 years or more. This is based on the type of game and size of the team. This game might not have super life like graphics, but as a programmer myself, I can see this game has so much depth to it that I'm not surprised its taking so long. To be honest I'm not sure how long it will take to finish but iI'm guessing it wont be soon, and thats not a bad thing! Not to mention people are chastising this game for having bugs.... I dont want to be mean but thats just stupid. Early access is almost guaranteed to have bugs, the whole point of going into Early Access is to fund the game, test the game, and also get input from the community on what they want added or changed in the game. The last comment I saw that really annoyed me was this ""it's more than likely that the developers are just going to abandon this game"". Where is the proof for this? I will admit that not all updates are monumental, but the devs have been so kind and listen to the community. Good things are worth waiting for. I have faith in this game and in the dev team. Oh and if you're more of a stickler for facts rather than opinions, which is fine, go to their website or a dev twitch stream. They actually have a development roadmap. It shows what they have done, and what they plan on doing."
