,Recommended,253250,33678810,Posted: 20 July,all,Raytings,"What’s Stonehearth?!  You mean Hearthstone? No…As the last known survivor of Radiant Entertainment, Stonehearth the village simulator has continued to be developed despite their buyout by RIOT Games and the cancellation of Rising Thunder.In Stonehearth you take the role as a master of your Hearthlings; you’ll select the jobs they hold, where they live, the kind of care they’ll receive, and more.  In some ways, you take the role as a great communist leader, but most people would put it in terms as a “god complex”.  The best way to describe the game: what if The Sims and Minecraft had a baby or in my case, adopted a cat (which by the way, you can do in Stonehearth randomly once you have a Shepard)  The objective is to make your settlement in “survival mode” more prosperous but enables the player to be creative at the same time.So this is a FULL game right?!  Tons of quality content?  Hold on there buddy…As of right now, Stonehearth is in development.  The game is available as an early access title, but it’s technically an alpha build.  There are plenty of bugs to go around like AI logic issues (make sure to report them via the game client w/ the ESC key), a lackluster of content currently available (more is planned, like a third human race, dwarves, more jobs, multiplayer, etc), and dead-end UI/clunky inventory management.   (most of the pop-ups don’t connect, causing you to sometimes skip around menus until you remember where to go).  Within 13 hours, I pretty much reached the full content of the game.Creative Artists that like to express themselves through pixel art, world building, and more will be happy to use the building design tool despite a few current bugs.  I found myself imagining all the art I’ve always wanted to create in Minecraft, but was too lazy to build block by block.  Once you finish designing your building, or placing down one of the default templates, your Hearthlings do all the building your available materials.  This tool is available in a non-creative only mode so it doesn’t feel like you’re cheating.  You can also export your designs by locating the files in the default directory, and share them with friends!(Steam\steamapps\common\Stonehearth\saved_objects\stonehearth\building_templates).Feel free to copy the following file of my Slime Pixel Art:https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B3TNsi-4EBwxNTZEUjFwS2FGZmcAlso, here is a community ran website for shared building plans::http://stonehearthbuilds.heliohost.org/While the mentioned content is lacking, there is still a good all-around vibe of the game, and things to come.  Already there are 16 mostly interesting jobs a Hearthling can work, from the basic “Worker” all the way to a Farmer or Engineer (TURNIP TURRETS!)  At least 50+ placeable items, and 100+ crafting ingredients collectable with the various jobs throughout the biome you pick.  With continuous updates to the community, you can’t help but get excited for the finished product.It’s hard for me to not recommend any piece of art, which I refer to games as.  However I want to underline, this game is not finished.  Only invest in the game if you’d like to support RIOT’s other endeavours, and a generally exciting game, or if you really want to see what beautiful stuff you could create with the building planner."
