76561198006833102,Recommended,253250,34652362,Posted: 31 August,all,jokeburner,"I have been following this game for over a year though it's development, so I feel I have played enough builds and hours of the game to give an educated review of this game.Synopsis: Stonehearth is a RTS Colony/Survival builder. While the gameplay loop of Building ->More Food ->More Colonists is solid, Stonehearth shines when it comes to precise building customization. Players can build structures of any kind based off the Custom Blueprint System. Players can spend hours on a single building, save it as a blueprint, and place their beautifully-crafted structures throughout the world. Players can also build squads of fighters with different specialities to do battle with monsters like goblins.PROS:Balanced RTS Colony/Survival gameplayHighly Detailed Custom StructuresMod Compatibility, and encouragement, allows for community supportWeekly updates with new content almost every monthCONSRandom bugs force players to save frequently (Bugs have significantly decreased in the past year to specific instances)Pathfinding AI is still an issue that forces players to fast-forward to complete tasksMining and building AI can cause tasks to become impossible to complete (This issue has been almost completely resolved in the past year's updates)Conclusion: Stonehearth is worth the price as long as the Radiant Team continues new content updates. It is definately a great value whenever it is on sale, but I feel that it is still a long way from the end of developement. It is an easy way to lose track of time and spend more time than expected building and ruling your settlement."
