,Not Recommended,253250,34845263,Posted: 9 September,all,thebigstickihityouwith,"I don't want to be negative about the game: It's clearly not finished. But for me, it's just the wrong side of not finished to be any fun.It's a base-builder, colony management game. And that's the problem.I'll give you an example of the building system, as it stands now:- To build a surrounding wall you need to lay the foundations - Love it! Brilliant!- Then you make the wall in sections of stone held between wooden pillars - That's just fine by me.- But then you finish the wall and you want to add a door. Oh dear.You can't modify the structure when it's finished. And guess what? You have to destroy the ENTIRE wall surrounding your colony because you can *select* one piece of wall but you can't *remove* just one piece of wall.Now that's a serious headache but it's made worse by the ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ AI who will seemingly go out of their way to get trapped behind the thing they're building. Whatever you do don't make a tower with a ladder but no door to the inside. Because you will have some ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ come along and build a roof over them so they're trapped forever. And you can just make a hole and let them out. You have to knock the whole tower down!Here's my next serious annoyance with the building system:- I made a building.- I decided to move a latern from one place to the side of my new building.- I changed my mind and (before it had been moved) relocated it somewhere else instead.- This left a ghost lattern attached to the original position.- It said do I want to remove it. I said yes. It knocked down my whole damn building. That's not how you cancel moving an object! Thatsanofair!On top of this majorly hammy building system the AI... Oh man... the AI... It's not the worst I've ever seen but it's not great either. What's the point of archers that won't take advantage of your tower? They'll just wander outside with the knights to die... So what's the point of building a tower? Well there isn't one, is there.Even with all these problems, after playing it for 10 hours or so, I've completed the tech-tree and become unfeasibly rich. I've only had one person die and that's because I wasn't aware they were dying.By the way: Don't expect anyone to rescue a downed colonist. Unless YOU explicitly tell them to, they'll leave them to die.  Because screw that guy, right?Oh and if you ask them to mine something above head height but don't make them a ladder, they won't make one themselves. Which is odd considering they make ladders all over the place when making buildings...I know... I know... The fanbois will be telling me how wrong I am about everything but trust me: Get Rimworld instead. Yeah. I said it."
