,Recommended,253250,35090460,Posted: 20 September,all,Shadow Star,"I totally recommend this game if you enjoy town building games. Compared to other games in similar fashion you also get random events and intruders and need to protect your town. You can even design your own buildings fairly easily. The game is als not very hard to learn. Get a stable food source, get some soldiers (Footmen) to protect your town, trade and let your mason/carpenter/blacksmith/engineer craft things.This game has a very cute voxel design and I really like it. It runs very stable for most of the time but once you reach 20 Hearthlings (which is max btw, hope it gets increased in the future) it can happen that the game slows down a bit, but restarting the game usually solved that for me.I do sometimes get error messages of which I am not sure why they happen or what causes them as I see nothing wrong. I only really had two game breaking bugs where one time the hud was not working correctly and the other where my footmen would fight enemies and neither would take damage resulting in an endless fight. Again restarting the game solved both of these bugs.I can only recommend this game and I am excited for what else the devs plan for the game in the future."
