,Recommended,253250,35094632,Posted: 20 September,all,Brewergamer,"Stonehearth is truly an amazing game, I have been following it for a while because I have loved the style of a town builder since I was a kid.  I finally decided to purchase it and I do not regret it one bit.  Stonehearth does really well and I was instantly addicted.  A little about the game:  when you start out you get a randomly generated crew of workers, whom you can later on assign roles (like blacksmith, farmer, etc) and you get to choose a randomly generated section of land to start out.  You gather, build, and defend your village from monsters.  All in all, would highly recommend."
